.TH "drm_fb_swab" 9 "drm_fb_swab" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_fb_swab \- Swap bytes into clip buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_fb_swab
.BI "(void *dst "  ","
.BI "void *src "  ","
.BI "struct drm_framebuffer *fb "  ","
.BI "struct drm_rect *clip "  ","
.BI "bool cached "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
Destination buffer
.IP "src" 12
Source buffer
.IP "fb" 12
DRM framebuffer
.IP "clip" 12
Clip rectangle area to copy
.IP "cached" 12
Source buffer is mapped cached (eg. not write-combined)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIcached\fP is false a temporary buffer is used to cache one pixel line at a
time to speed up slow uncached reads.

This function does not apply clipping on dst, i.e. the destination
is a small buffer containing the clip rect only.
